- Text: Why Use this Toolkit?
Task Risk Assessment (TRA) and Dynamic Risk Assessment (DRA) are critical
components of a robust safety management system, playing a pivotal role in preventing
workplace accidents and ensuring compliance with regulatory requirements.
This toolkit provides teams with:
•
A clear process, supported by templates, which enable effective and consistent
risk assessments.
•
Greater insight into potential risks and hazards.
•
Enhanced operational safety through the implementation of appropriate risk
controls.
•
A consistent, reliable way to evaluate whether a task is safe to proceed, or whether
additional risk controls are required.
How to Use this Toolkit
The toolkit is designed to be used by frontline teams and supervisors. It contains:
•
A Task Risk Assessment (TRA) checklist, covering all relevant aspects of a task.
•
A Dynamic Risk Assessment (DRA) template, enabling teams to identify and
assess risks in real time.
•
Guidance on how to complete both the TRA and DRA.
To make the most of this toolkit, it is essential that all users are properly trained in
how to use the TRA checklist and DRA template.
