5. What is a Task Risk Assessment (TRA)?
A TRA is a short, task-specific risk assessment carried out immediately before work
begins, focusing on the actual conditions at the point of work.
6. Step-by-Step TRA Process
Step 1: Stop & Think
0
Do I understand the task?
Is there an approved method statement / permit?
Step 2: Identify Hazards
What could cause harm?
What has changed since planning?
Step 3: Assess the Risk
0
How likely is harm?
•
What would the consequence be?
Step 4: Apply Controls
•
Are existing controls in place?
Do additional controls need to be applied?
Step 5: Confirm Understanding
•
Has the team been briefed?
•
Does everyone understand their role?
Step 6: Proceed or Stop
